&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a Band 6 post but we would welcome Band 5 applicants looking for a development opportunity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is based at Stratton Hospital Minor Injuries Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stratton Minor Injuries Unit have a Part time vacancy. This is a rare opportunity to work within a sought after urgent care environment. The unit is practitioner-led and is committed to delivering high quality care to the local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested in interviewing a range of candidates:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aspiring practitioners with an urgent care background who would like to develop further and obtain degree level qualifications (Band 5 development post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practitioners able to work in an advanced practice role which includes minor injury and illness with some paediatric experience (Band 6)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When applying please make it clear which position you are applying for.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to have a passion for minor injury care, good communication skills, and a commitment to providing excellent care as part of the MIU team. You must be responsive to change and flexible in your approach. A sound knowledge of professional issues will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post is 30 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Coleman MIU Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01288 320101 / 01288 320100&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rebecca.coleman6@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
